During my recent trip to Los Angeles, Lyle and Erik Menendez were all anyon=
e wanted to talk about. The brothers, convicted in 1999 for the brutal murd=
er of their parents in their Beverly Hills mansion, are now seen in a more =
sympathetic light, thanks largely to Ryan Murphy=E2=80=99s Netflix series M=
onsters: The Lyle and Erik Menendez Story, and Alejandro Hartmann=E2=80=99s=
 Netflix documentary, The Menendez Brothers, which explores the severe abus=
e they allegedly suffered at the hands of their father, Jos=C3=A9, a former=
 RCA Records executive. Indeed, the question on everyone=E2=80=99s mind=E2=
=80=94from folks at CAA to Uber drivers to the brothers=E2=80=99 outspoken =
celebrity advocate ( https://www.nbcnews.com/news/kim-kardashian-free-menen=
dez-brothers-rcna173638?utm_campaign=3DWhat+I%27m+Hearing%2B+-+SUBSCRIBERS+=
%2810%2F29%2F24%29&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io ), Kim Kardashian=E2=80=94was w=
hether the Menendezes would be released. Last Thursday, over the objections=
 of some L.A. prosecutors, L.A. District Attorney George
Gasc=C3=B3n announced plans to seek the brothers=E2=80=99 resentencing, a m=
ove that could=E2=80=94pending a judge=E2=80=99s approval=E2=80=94free the =
duo after decades in prison.

The timing of Gasc=C3=B3n=E2=80=99s decision, coming just days before an el=
ection in which he=E2=80=99s significantly behind in the polls, has drawn c=
riticism from his opponent, Nathan Hochman. =E2=80=9CHe=E2=80=99s 30 points=
 down in the polls, and he=E2=80=99s doing this now because he wants to dis=
tract voters from a record of public safety failure with a made-for-TV medi=
a event,=E2=80=9D Hochman told me in a phone interview. Nevertheless, the D=
=2EA. race has cast a light on Hollyw=
ood=E2=80=99s quiet shift away from the
more progressive policies that got Gasc=C3=B3n elected four years ago=E2=80=
=94ending cash bail, ordering prosecutors not to seek enhanced sentences fo=
r prior convictions or gang affiliations, etcetera.

Hochman remained noncommittal about whether he would have advocated for the=
 Menendez brothers=E2=80=99 release. =E2=80=9CI have no idea,=E2=80=9D he t=
old me. =E2=80=9CNo one should weigh in on that decision unless they=E2=80=
=99ve thoroughly reviewed the case.=E2=80=9D But he pointed out that the ha=
beas petition was filed back in May 2023 and suggested that Gasc=C3=B3n, af=
ter delaying a response for 18 months, could have waited until November 26,=
 long after the election, when a Los Angeles judge was already scheduled to=
 discuss the brothers=E2=80=99 fate at a hearing.

It=E2=80=99s unlikely that Gasc=C3=B3n=E2=80=99s decision to revisit the Me=
nendez case, however popular it may be, will do much for his electoral chan=
ces. Four years after coming to office with a progressive agenda, he faces =
immense backlash over the
perception that his policies have made Los Angeles less safe. The tradition=
ally liberal circles of entertainment and fashion=E2=80=94people like Jimmy=
 Iovine, Peter Guber, and Alex von F=C3=BCrstenburg=E2=80=94have moved thei=
r support to Hochman. =E2=80=9CWhile I absolutely have a history of being a=
 hard-core Democrat, I had to take a real look at Nathan=E2=80=99s platform=
 and the state of our city at present,=E2=80=9D Laura Wasser, the prominent=
